
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Conan Fitness Company

class Person {
  +firstName: String
  +familyName: String
  +birthDate: Date
}

class Trainer {
  +diploma: String
}

class Member {
  +memberId: Integer
}

class Prospect {
  +prospectId: Integer
}

class Center {
  +name: String
  +address: String
  +rooms: List<Room>
}

class Room {
  +roomNumber: Integer
  +maxCapacity: Integer
}

class Session {
  +date: Date
  +startTime: Time
  +room: Room
  +center: Center
}

class GroupSession {
  +sessionType: String
  +trainer: Trainer
}

class IndividualSession {
}

class Intern {
  +internId: Integer
}

' Inheritance and Associations
Person <|-- Member
Person <|-- Trainer
Person <|-- Prospect
Trainer <|-- Intern

Center "1" *-- "0..*" Room

Session <|-- GroupSession
Session <|-- IndividualSession

GroupSession "1" --> "1" Trainer
Session "1" --> "1" Room
Session "1" --> "1" Center

Person "0..*" --> "0..*" Session
Trainer "0..*" --> "0..*" GroupSession
Intern "0..*" --> "0..*" GroupSession

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **`Person`** is a base class with subclasses:
  - `Member`
  - `Trainer`
  - `Prospect`

- **`Trainer`** has a subclass `Intern`.

- A **`Center`** has many **`Room`**s.

- A **`Session`** can be either a **`GroupSession`** or an **`IndividualSession`**.

- Each **`GroupSession`** must be supervised by one **`Trainer`**.

- Each **`Session`** must be associated with one **`Room`** and one **`Center`**.

- A **`Person`** (including `Member`, `Trainer`, `Prospect`) can participate in zero or more **`Sessions`**.

This model ensures that all the requirements are captured, including people who have not participated yet and trainers who have not supervised any session.